-- Tottenham Offers Juventus’s Pirlo Three-Year Contact, Star Says
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-26T13:28:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-26/tottenham-offers-juventus-s-pirlo-three-year-contact-star-says.html
Tottenham has offered  Andrea Pirlo  a
three-year contract as part of its effort to sign the Juventus
midfielder, the Daily Star said.  Spurs’ technical director Franco Baldini and manager Andre
Vilas-Boas made the move as they look to have an agreement for
the Italy international, whose contract expires after this
seaosn, in place by January, the Star said.  Arsenal, Chelsea and Manchester United are also monitoring
the 34-year-old, but have yet to make an offer, the newspaper
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  